------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Number of tokens to add to bucket each time it is subject to a periodic update (PUP).

The rate (tokens per second) with which tokens are added to the bucket is:
   PUP_TOKENS x clk_frequency / PUP_INTERVAL 

A bucket can be configured to be permanently open by setting
PUP_TOKENS=0x1fff
When permanently open, no tokens are subtracted from the bucket and PUP will set the number of tokens in the bucket to THRES. No inheritance will occur when a bucket is permanently open.
To configure a DLB to be permanently open, PUP_TOKENS must be set to 0x1fff for both the CIR bucket and the EIR bucket. 
Setting only CIR bucket or only EIR bucket to 0x1fff is not a valid configuration.

Related parameters:
ANA_AC_SDLB:LBGRP_TBL:PUP_INTERVAL.PUP_INTERVAL
